-- Mitsubishi Electric Sets Up Turkish Division to Expand in Region
-- B y   E r c a n   E r s o y
-- 2013-01-08T15:03:09Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-01-08/mitsubishi-electric-sets-up-turkish-division-to-expand-in-region.html
Mitsubishi Electric Corp. (6503)  opened a
unit in Istanbul to expand its electronic business in  Turkey  and
surrounding regions.  Mitsubishi Electric Turkey AS is 70 percent owned by
European division Mitsubishi Electric Europe BV and the
remainder is held by the parent, according to a  statement  on the
Japanese company’s website. Kei Uruma is president for the
Turkey unit.  Mitsubishi Electric’s business in Turkey includes air
conditioning, factory automation and products such as
satellites, elevators, escalators and electrical equipment for
railcars, according to the statement. Sales totaled about $112
million in Turkey in the fiscal year that ended March 2012.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ercan Ersoy in Istanbul at 
